definition.value: A  tetrachlorobenzene carrying chloro groups at positions 1, 2 , 3 and 4.

An olefinic compound that is ethene is which a hydrogen at position 1 is replaced by a 4-carboxyphenyl group and a hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a 5,5,8,8-tetramethyl-3-[(1H-pyrazol-1-yl)methyl]-5,6,7,8-tetrahydronaphthalen-2-yl group (the E-stereoisomer). It is a selective retinoic acid receptor gamma (RARgamma) agonist developed by Ipsen, to reduce the formation of new heterotopic ossification in adults and children with fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva (FOP), a rare bone disorder.
